snippet.textDisplay: California is the coolest place on Earth. I like to think of California, Nevada, and Arizona as my three favorite places. The Los Angeles area has In-N-Out, Original Tommy’s, Fatburger, and Jack In The Box. Plus, theme parks such as Disneyland and Universal Studios Hollywood. The Las Vegas Area has those chains too, but also has M&M’s World, Hershey’s Chocolate World, and a Coca-Cola store. Arizona has Smith’s Food And Drug Marketplace (similar to Smith’s Marketplace in Vegas.) Also, LOL! My keyboard thinks I’m Italian. It keeps trying to put A in between every few syllables.

snippet.textDisplay: Thank you KTLA for uploading this to YouTube!  My TV provider (YouTube TV) does not carry KTLA and trying to watch the parade on ABC was painful.  No other broadcaster can compare to KTLA in covering the Rose Parade, which I've watched every New Year's Day for 40+ years.  Even when I watch the parade in person, I re-watch it again on KTLA for their excellent coverage and commentary.
